unitsInfo.content.value:
Note 1: AU means Astronomical Unit, which is the average distance from the Sun to Earth, roughly 150 million km.

Note 2: The mass values in this simulation range from 1 Jupiter mass to 1.5 Solar masses. And although planets, comets and asteroids have much smaller masses than this, all astronomical objects show a similar behavior under a strong gravitational field.
